      'result': \"\"\"CVE-2006-2369 is a vulnerability affecting RealVNC 4.1.1 and other products that integrate RealVNC, such as AdderLink IP and Cisco CallManager. This flaw allows remote attackers to bypass authentication.

The authentication bypass occurs when a client requests an insecure security type, specifically "Type 1 - None". The affected software accepts this insecure security type even if the server has not explicitly offered it. This vulnerability was initially demonstrated using a long password.

The vulnerability has a CVSS 2.0 Base Score of 7.5 (High severity) with a vector of AV:N/AC:L/Au:N/C:P/I:P/A:P. For CVSS 3.0, it has a Base Score of 9.8 (Critical severity) with a vector of CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H. Public exploits for CVE-2006-2369 exist, including Metasploit modules like "RealVNC NULL Authentication Mode Bypass" and "VNC Authentication None Detection". The Exploit Prediction Scoring System (EPSS) score for this CVE is 91.15%, indicating a high probability of exploitation activity.\"\"\"
    }
  )
)] role='user'
